Lecturers in Civil,Construction Engineering &Quantity; Surveying
- ,
Date Posted: 2014/05/01 05:53:51
Ref. JB3046142
Job Description
Appointees will be required to lecture and carry out all academic activities in the department including teaching, supervision of degree and/ or masters projects, academic guidance, examining and development of learning support materials.
Skills
Candidates must have attained a minimum of a master's degree in the relevant specialization and have a minimum of 5 years of experience in the higher education level.
Additional industrial experience will be an advantage.
Candidates must clearly indicate the post for which they wish to be considered by quoting the reference number for the job. Reference number for this job is REF Number: CCE 02052014.
Terms and Conditions: Successful candidates are normally offered two year renewable contracts. Salaries are commensurate with the post and experience. Other benefits are as per Oman labour law and also include medical insurance, airfares, 45 days of annual leave, and end of term benefits.
Education
PG - Master of Technology/Engineering in Civil, Construction Engineering
